Rassie Erasmus has made his first appearance since the confirmation of his appointment as the new Bok coach on Thursday morning. JOHANNESBURG - New Springbok Coach Rassie Erasmus says he's aware of the problems with South African Rugby and fixing them will be a huge challenge. Erasmus has made his first appearance since confirmation of his appointment on Thursday morning. The 45-year-old has a six-year contract that will run until the end of the 2023 Rugby World Cup But Erasmus says he believes the Springboks have the power to win the event in Japan. “I think we’ve got players and the IP [intellectual property] who can win the world cup, [the question is] how quickly can we align the players' talent, IP and coaches, working together in South Africa? If we can do that quickly, I think we have a big chance.”  